==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: grand unification theory
<hw>grand unification
theory</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Theoretical physics)</fld>
<def>Any of a class of physics theories that attempts to explain the
electroweak forces, strong force, and gravitation within a single
mathematical conceptual scheme. In the 1990's <stype>string
theory</stype> and <stype>superstring theory</stype> were prominent
examples. Abbreviated <abbr>GUT</abbr>, plural
<abbr>GUTs</abbr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grane</ent>⟦br⟧
